  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) the <strong>garlic</strong></p>\n<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>garlic</strong>, <strong>panko breadcrumbs</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until they're golden</p>\n<p>Once done, transfer to a bowl and set aside for later</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/red-pepper-and-sausage-pasta-garlic-crumb/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut the <strong>Cumberland sausages</strong> into bite-sized pieces</p>\n<p>Wipe the pan clean and return to a medium-high heat with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong></p>\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped sausages</strong> and cook for 4-5 min or until they're browned</p>\n<p> </p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/red-pepper-and-sausage-pasta-garlic-crumb/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, boil a kettle</p>\n<p>Peel and finely slice the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\n<p>Deseed the<strong> red pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/red-pepper-and-sausage-pasta-garlic-crumb/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, transfer the <strong>sausages</strong> to a plate and set them aside </p>\n<p>Return the pan to a medium heat, add the <strong>sliced</strong><strong> onion</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 5-6 min or until starting to soften</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/red-pepper-and-sausage-pasta-garlic-crumb/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>tortiglioni</strong> <strong>pasta </strong>to a pot of <strong>boiled water</strong> with a large pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\n<p>Cook the<strong> pasta</strong> for 10-12 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p>\n<p>Once done, reserve 100ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml]</span> of the<strong> starchy pasta water </strong>and drain the <strong>pasta</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/red-pepper-and-sausage-pasta-garlic-crumb/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the<strong> tomato paste</strong>, <strong>dried oregano</strong> and <strong>balsamic vinegar</strong> to the peppers and onion</p>\n<p>Return the <strong>sausages</strong> to the pan and crumble in 1/2 <span class=\"text-danger\">[1]</span> <strong>chicken stock cube</strong> </p>\n<p>Add the <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong>, a pinch of<strong> sugar </strong>and a good grind of<strong> black pepper</strong> and cook for 6-7 min or until a <strong>thick pasta sauce</strong> remains</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/red-pepper-and-sausage-pasta-garlic-crumb/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, once the <strong>pasta sauce</strong> has thickened, stir through the<strong> pasta</strong></p>\n<p>Add the <strong>reserved starchy pasta water</strong> to the pasta and give everything a good mix up</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/red-pepper-and-sausage-pasta-garlic-crumb/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> red pepper &amp; sausage pasta</strong> and garnish with the<strong> garlic breadcrumbs</strong></p>\n<p>Enjoy! </p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
